examples.en: Does he have enough dexterity to cope with a job like that?
He's a teacher known for his imagination and verbal dexterity.
He carried a crutch, which he managed with wonderful dexterity.
He has the dexterity needed to deal cards quickly.
He can do any sort of work requiring handiness and dexterity.
No great manual dexterity (=skill in using your hands) is required to perform the technique.
